#DOC id=26--workspaces--design-system-system source=/root/yvon/docs/briefs/lifeos-reference/26--workspaces--design-system-system.md format=toon-doc compressed=2026-06-12T06:40:26.304Z

S|# 26 · Workspaces & Design System (System)|> The multi-workspace ("multi-tenant") model that lets one Mission Control run several businesses — each with its own theme, pages, agents, and partner logins — on a shared Supabase backend.
S|Purpose|LifeOS is built as a **multi-workspace** app. Each business/project is a **workspace** with its own visual design, page structure, workflows, and partner access, while sharing the common agt roster, mem system, and command center. This is what makes it scale from one founder to a portfolio of companies.
S|Workspace switcher|- Top of the sidebar: a **WORKSPACE** selector (active = "Vibe with AI") with chevrons to switch. // - Switching changes the **data**, the **theme**, and can change the **available pages/workflows** for that project.
S|The workspaces & their themes|\| Workspace \| Business \| Theme \| Notes \| // \|---\|---\|---\|---\| // \| **Vibe with AI** \| main brand \| default violet/magenta \| the owner's primary workspace; current mockups all share this look \| // \| **Canela** \| e-commerce shop \| **"deep sea" greenish** \| distinct palette \| // \| **Valhalla** \| music business \| **"techno"** (electronic) \| fits electronic music brand \| // \| **By Design** \| app / agency \| **"glass neon"** \| \| // > Each workspace has a **unique, cool des
S|Multi-tenant / partner access (stated)|- Built on **Supabase**. // - **Each project gets its own login.** Partners receive a login that **uniquely grants access to one workspace** (their company's workspace only). // - The owner retains the **overview of all projects/workspaces**, while partners are scoped to their single workspace. // - This is what the **visibility scoping** in Brain & Wiki (Private / Team / Workspace / Cross-workspace) ties into.
S|Why it matters|It cleanly separates per-business identity and access while reusing the shared brain, agents, and command-center patterns — a true multi-tenant operating system for a portfolio of one-person-plus-agents businesses.